cement hook can read and enforce.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure boundary is the contract between two hooks communicating through a shared state file: the PostToolUse hook writes it, and the pre-tool enforcement hook reads and acts on it. A schema mismatch or wrong field name would cause silent enforcement failure. Testing either hook alone cannot catch this. REAL-INFRA: Requires a real temp filesystem; no network or subprocess. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking file I/O in either hook would always pass and hide format mismatches. LLM-DEP: No LLM. INTEGRATION-CHECK (Down-test): Cannot reproduce with one function — both hooks must participate. (Up-test): In-process wiring through a real temp directory is sufficient; no subprocess or OS-level behavior needed. Integration survives.","test_description":"Run the PostToolUse hook's state-writing logic with a detected PR-create event, writing to a temp directory. Then run the pre-tool enforcement hook's state-reading logic against the same temp directory. Assert that the enforcement hook (a) successfully parses the state file without error, and (b) produces an 'enforce review gate' decision (not 'no gate'). Both hooks must run; the test fails if either the format is unreadable or the enforcement decision is wrong.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9650,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9650},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88b3a286-77cf-4145-a745-b10a41137992","uuid":"05046a8d-fd4d-466b-a8c7-0054baf609de"}
